Suppose the consumer, service locator, service provider, and service provider interface
are each in separate modules. Which of the following best describes the following
module-info file?
module nature.tree {
provides nature.sapling.Tree with nature.tree.Maple;
}

questions.explanation:
The Maple class is intended to be an implementation of the Tree interface. However, this
interface needs to be accessible. This module is missing a requires nature.sapling;
statement, making option E the correct answer.

